name: Humanfly II Vinyl LP (gatefold) PROG 01
description: Total Prog's first release. Recorded and Mastered by Ben Gardner (That Fucking Tank, Pulled Apart By Horses). This is the bands second recording and came out in 2007. It was immediately bummed by all the glossy mags for its ultra trendy post metal tendencies and its progtastic atmospherics. Shortly after its release, 20 Buck Spin (Coffins, the Obsessed, Black Bones Angel) asked if they could put out the CD version. The Band embraced this opportunity and the CD version + 2 bonus tracks followed shortly after.

name: Electric Mud Generator - To The Disdain of Polyhymnia CD PROG 02
description: TOTAL PROG are proud to present the EMG recording in all its heavenly glory. Behold it's fantastic prog/doom riffage and superb artwork (Chris - Narcosis). Get down with the beautiful atmospheric qualities and orgasmicly tasty licks. Awesome.

name: Humanfly/ Queen of Swords - Split LP
description:
Mastered by James Plotkin (Khanate, Scorn, Old, Phantomsmasher)

Leeds' HUMANFLY deliver possibly their most pummeling tracks to date! 21+ minutes of glorious progressive riffage through various changing moods.
1. Marrakech  
2. An Intimate Battering

London's QUEEN OF SWORDS' debut release. A single 13 minute track in 2 parts, From deep synthesizer pulses, astral tones and precise pounding drums to hovering Sine waves, granular clouds of sound & distant analogue bleeps.

name: Humanfly II - CD (20 buck spin)
description:
Formed in the early part of the decade, the band offer epic, metallic journeys through huge heaviness and Floyd esq atmospherics. Vocals are used sparingly, focusing primarily on building thematically through the music. The  CD release of II by US label 20 Buck Spin has introduced Humanfly to a larger audience due to the international distribution.

2 bonus tracks from split with Queen of Swords.

name: Human/Floyd T-shirt (only small left)
